<HEADLINE>
FT  26 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Bell Cablemedia plans listing
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Cable operator Bell Cablemedia plans to list its shares in London in the
first quarter of 1995, according to chief financial officer Mr William
Anderson, Reuter reports.
'We have a very strong corporate commitment (to a UK listing),' Mr Anderson
said.
In July, Bell Cablemedia, which groups the UK cable interests of Bell Canada
International, Cable and Wireless of the UK and Jones Intercable of the US,
raised Dollars 479m (Pounds 303m) via a flotation on the Nasdaq stock
exchange in the US.
TeleWest, the largest UK cable operator, last week said it planned a
flotation this year, which is expected to raise between Pounds 300m and
Pounds 370m.
