<HEADLINE>
FT  26 OCT 94 / International Company News: Securities losses take toll on
Kemper
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   NEW YORK
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Kemper, the US financial services group which has agreed to a takeover by
life insurance group Conseco, reported third-quarter operating earnings of
Dollars 32.7m on its continuing operations, which before one-off factors
were flat compared with a year ago.
Mr David Mathis, chairman, said the earnings partly reflected the 'unusual
conditions' and 'overall distraction' of the third quarter, when the company
agreed to a deal with Conseco to fend off a hostile bid from GE Capital.
The figures included a Dollars 40m investment loss from the sale of
corporate bonds and collateralised mortgage obligations, derivative-type
securities which have caused losses at several US financial institutions
this year.
Results were also hit by a Dollars 3m loss in the company's broking
business, reflecting lower commissions.
Overall net income was Dollars 17.5m, or 34 cents a share. A year ago, net
income of Dollars 162.4m, or Dollars 3.63, reflected a number of one-off
factors.
</TEXT>
