<HEADLINE>
FT  26 OCT 94 / Role of Scottish secretary queried
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The need for a secretary of state for Scotland would be sharply reduced if a
Scottish parliament were formed, a group of leading Scots said yesterday.
A report by the Scottish constitutional commission says that if a Scottish
parliament were established, executive responsibility for the Scottish
Office would pass to it from the Scottish secretary.
Labour is pledged to establish a Scottish parliament in its first
parliamentary session.
</TEXT>
