<HEADLINE>
FT  26 OCT 94 / Kuwait orders missiles
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Shorts, the Belfast-based aerospace company, has received a Pounds 50m order
for air defence missiles from Kuwait.
The announcement of the order came at the end of a visit to the emirate by
Mr Malcolm Rifkind, defence secretary.
Shorts said the contract would not affect plans to cut 240 jobs at its plant
in Belfast.
The order - for the Starburst shoulder-launched anti-aircraft missile - was
said to be a surprise to the Ministry of Defence, the Defence Export
Services Organisation and Shorts.
Starburst - the immediate successor to the Javelin system, which Shorts has
sold to more than 10 countries - has been developed to destroy
high-performance low-flying aircraft as well as helicopters.
