FT  26 OCT 94 / Japanese politician sentenced
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By WILLIAM DAWKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   TOKYO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A former provincial governor, the only Japanese politician brought to trial
in a scandal involving Sagawa Kyubin parcel delivery company, yesterday
received a suspended prison sentence. Mr Kiyoshi Kaneko was given a one-year
jail term suspended for three years, for taking Y100m (Pounds 632,100) from
Sagawa Kyubin in a political funding scandal that helped bring down two
governments. Disclosures over Sagawa Kyubin's donations to senior
politicians in 1992 and 1993 contributed to the collapse of the Liberal
Democratic party government last year.
