<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 94 / UK Company News: Sanderson Elect
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sanderson Electronics, the computer software and hardware company, is set to
double its sales with the acquisition of a controlling interest in SGA
Pacific from General Automation.
It is paying Pounds 3.42m for a 51 per cent stake which will take its total
holding to 78 per cent, or 72 per cent fully diluted. The deal will result
in Sanderson's turnover rising to Pounds 55m. In the six months to March 31
turnover was Pounds 14.2m.
The consideration is being satisfied by Dollars 1m (Pounds 600,000) cash,
Dollars 1m loan notes and the transfer of 4.1m of GAI's shares.
SGA supplies computer software and hardware in Australia, New Zealand,
Singapore and Hong Kong.
