<HEADLINE>
FT  25 OCT 94 / International Company News: Clean-up costs take toll on
Asarco result
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LAURIE MORSE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Asarco, the US copper mining company, reported a Dollars 16.1m net loss in
the third quarter, in spite of rising metals prices, writes Laurie Morse.
The loss, which amounted to 39 cents a share, was the result of a previously
announced charge of Dollars 45.5m to clean up a closed smelter site in
Tacoma, Washington.
Without the charge, Asarco would have earned Dollars 14.6m, or 35 cents a
share, on sales of Dollars 513m, compared with last year's third-quarter
loss of Dollars 3m, or 8 cents, on sales of Dollars 425m.
For the first nine months of the year, Asarco reported net earnings of
Dollars 15.8m, or 38 cents a share, on sales of Dollars 1.4bn.
This compares with last year's loss of Dollars 58m, or Dollars 1.40 a share,
on sales of Dollars 1.3bn.
</TEXT>
